# Home Assistant Add-on: RustDesk Server

[![GitHub Release][releases-shield]][releases]
[![License][license-shield]][license]

Self-hosted [RustDesk][rustdesk] server (hbbs + hbbr) for your own
remote desktop relay.

## About

This add-on lets you self-host the signaling (`hbbs`) and relay (`hbbr`)
servers required by RustDesk clients. The public RustDesk servers are meant
for testing only and are not sized for production traffic - running your own
server gives you predictable performance and keeps your remote-desktop traffic
on infrastructure you control.

